title: Deadly shark always has a smile on her face | Daily Mail Online
text: comments A female shark off the coast of Florida has caught the eye of divers across the nation thanks to her toothy smile that looks reminiscent of Bruce from the hit film Finding Nemo. Many divers hope to catch a glimpse of the happy predator, nicknamed Snooty, just off the coast of Jupiter, Florida. Photographer Cassie Jensen had been wanting to see the Lemon shark for 'years' and was amazed to see she actually does look like the Finding Nemo character. A female shark off the coast of Florida has caught the eye of divers across the United States because of her toothy smile Many divers say the shark, nicknamed Snooty, resembles the shark Bruce from Finding Nemo Many divers hope to catch a glimpse of the happy predator, nicknamed Snooty, just off the coast of Jupiter, Florida Bruce, a shark in the hit film Finding Nemo, is memorable for his large toothy smile full of rows of teeth Cassie said: 'I have been diving with many sharks before, but this was the first time I had ever met Snooty. 'I've been wanting to meet her for a long time, so when I saw her cruise by me, my heart began to race. 'She is a well known shark in Florida waters for the way her jaw is set, causing her to constantly look like she is smiling. 'She also has a crimped tail but it doesn't seem to bother her, and we love her even more for it. 'She's always smiling and happy to be around us!' Photographer Cassie Jensen had been wanting to see her for years when she finally came across the unique shark The photographer said she was amazed when she saw that Snooty truly does resemble the computer-generated character from Finding Nemo Jenson said that Snooty also seems to have a crimped tail, but it doesn't seem to bother the shark RELATED ARTICLES
